ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I felt keyed up or on edge because I was worried about things
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I felt very fidgety, making it difficult to sit still
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I had difficulty concentrating because my mind was on my worries
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I worried a lot that something bad might happen
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: When I was extremely anxious, I was afraid I would lose control
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I felt sad or depressed
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I was not as interested in my usual activities
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I did not feel like eating; my appetite was poor.
Notes: 0 = Rarely or none of the time (less than 1 day); 1 = Some or a little of the time (1-2 days); 2 = Occasionally or a moderate amount of time (3-4 days); 3 = Most or all of the time (5-7 days); 4 = Nearly every day for 2 weeks; 99 = Prefer not to answer; 999= NA/NK/missing; 888 = Skipped ; 777 = Condition Skipped ; 555 = Missing

ElementDescription: My appetite was much greater than usual
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I had difficulty sleeping
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I was sleeping too much
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I felt physically slowed down, like my body wasstuck in mud
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: My energy level was low
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I felt guilty
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I thought I was a failure
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I had problems concentrating
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I had more difficulties making decisions than usual
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I wished I were dead.
Notes: 0 = Rarely or none of the time (less than 1 day); 1 = Some or a little of the time (1-2 days); 2 = Occasionally or a moderate amount of time (3-4 days); 3 = Most or all of the time (5-7 days); 4 = Nearly every day for 2 weeks; 999= NA/NK/missing; 444 = Do not wish to respond; 999 = No Answer; 888 = Skipped; 777 = Condition Skipped; 555 = Missing

ElementDescription: I thought about killing myself
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: I thought that the future looked hopeless
Notes: 0 = Not at all (0 days), 1 = Rarely true (1-2 days), 2 = Sometimes true (3-4 days), 3 = Often true (5-6 days), 4 = Almost always true (every day)

ElementDescription: Overall, how much have symptoms of depression interfered with or caused difficulties in your life during the past week?
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 1= A little bit; 2= A moderate amount; 3= Quite a bit; 4= Extremely

ElementDescription: How would you rate your overall quality of life during the past week
Notes: 0= Very good, my life could hardly be better; 1= Pretty good, most things are going well; 2= The good and bad parts are about equal; 3= Pretty bad, most things are going poorly; 4= Very bad, my life could hardly be worse

ElementDescription: CUDOS Total Score
Notes: 0-10 = non-depressed; 11-20 = minimal depression; 21-30 = mild depression; 31-45 = moderate depression; 46-72 = severe depression
